The Department of State Services (DSS) has said stakeholders in the transport and logistics sector must contribute to the security of the 2019 general election. The Director of the DSS, Institute for Security Studies (ISS) Ayodele Adeleke made this known yesterday during the opening ceremony of a two-day Security Awareness Seminar for Critical Stakeholders, held in Abuja. He said stakeholders such as the National Union of Road Transport Workers (NURTW) and The Nigeria Union of Petroleum and Natural Gas Workers (NUPENG) among others, are critical to the security and success of the election. He noted that they are important in planning for the movement of materials and personnel in the election process and should not be undermined. He said, “The seminar is designed to create awareness among critical state holders in the transport and logistics sector, civil society organizations and the general populace on possible threats to the 2019 elections.” He said the DSS through organizing such seminar is taking all measures to contain potential threats to the electoral process. 2019 elections:  DSS sensitizes transport sector stakeholders Lagos CP warns transport unions on violence during elections 4,000 security personnel deployed for Jigawa LG polls